{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Each FFTr layer is composed of a 1-D conv with kernel size 3 and 384/1536 input/output channels, ReLU activation, a 1-D conv with kernel size 3 and 1536/384 input/output filters, followed by Dropout and Layer Norm.",
    "Duration Predictor and Pitch Predictor have the same architecture: a 1-D conv with kernel size 3 and 384/256 channels, and a 1-D conv with 256/256 channels, each followed by ReLU, Layer Norm and Dropout layers.",
    "The last layer projects every 256-channel vector to a scalar.",
    "Dropout rate is 0.1, also on attention heads.All described models were trained on graphemes.",
    "Training on phonemes leads to a similar quality of a model, with either Tacotron 2 or Montreal Forced Aligner [18] durations."
  ],
